name: yhangry
headline: Marketplace for private chefs
description:
Yhangry is a private chef marketplace, where you can book a chef whenever you want to socialize at home.

For $40pp, you can book a 3-course feast in just a few clicks. On the supply side, we help chefs earn 3 times as much as working in a restaurant.

founders.name: Heinin Zhang, Founder
founders.description: I'm the Co-founder and Co-CEO of yhangry. I grew up in Germany and China and I studied Philosophy and Economics at the London School of Economics, before starting my career on the trading floor at Goldman Sachs. I'm a big foodie and wine-lover but always too busy to cook for my friends, hence yhangry to the rescue. In my free time, I compete my horse in eventing.

founders.name: Siddhi Mittal, Founder
founders.description: I'm the Co-Founder and Co CEO of yhangry. I grew up in India, studied Computer Science (Artificial Intelligence) @ Columbia University in New York, and love to solve real-life problems using technology. Before yhangry, I was a credit trader for over six years, running over $700m of credit risk (across mortgages and financial credit). I'm also a (competitive) Bollywood dancer and a major coffee addict that brews her own barista coffee.

## Why hire private chef for your event with yhangry
### Vetted and rated professional chefs
We work with the best chefs and we make choosing the right chef easy by providing transparent ratings and reviews by real customers.
### Secure payment & protection
At Yhangry, all payments are securely held in escrow until after your event. This ensures your funds are protected, minimizing any risks. Whether your concern is a no-show chef or a bad experience, pay securely through the platform for peace of mind.
### Public liability insurance cover
Any accidents, caused by the chef during an event booked on the yhangry platform is covered by our public liability policy. We’ve made it our mission to give you peace of mind.
### BNPL or split the bill with your guests
If you are booking your event more than 5 weeks in advance, you can pay a 10% deposit or use our split bill feature instead of making the full payment upfront.
### Flexible cancellation policy
If a chef cancels, we will help you find a new chef and if that’s not possible you will receive a full refund, no need to worry about losing any money. If you need to cancel, you will get a 100% refund until 7 days before your event.
### Dedicated customer support
Contact Us via email at info@yhangry.com, phone at [020 4525 5238](http://www.yhangry.com/<tel:02045255238>) or Whatsapp at [+447418310743](http://www.yhangry.com/<tel:+447418310743>)

## Frequently asked questions
#### Still have questions?
Can't find the answer you're looking for? Please chat to our friendly team.
[Contact us](http://www.yhangry.com/</contact>)
How much is a private/personal chef in the UK?
Customers booking a private or personal chef for an event usually spend £700 for a group of 10 people. The per person pricing varies depending on the number of people and the particular chef's minimum spend.
What is included in the costs of a private chef?
The cost of a private chef covers the cost of Ingredients, meal preparation, cooking, serving, and cleanup.
What equipment do I need to provide for the private chefs?
Mostly yhangry private chefs carry their own equipment, so you won't need to assist with any. However, ensuring the basic cooking amenities like blenders, stoves and crockery are available is essential.
Do I need to provide ingredients or the private chef will get it?
You can provide your own ingredients if you're seeking to lower the overall expense. However, yhangry private chefs mostly bring their own freshly-sourced ingredients and premium-quality meats to prepare scrumptious meals.
What type of ingredients do the private chefs use?
Most chefs have their favourite suppliers for specific produce. Simply ask the chef you're looking to book about where they source their produce and let them know if you have a particular preference, e.g. for organic ingredients.
Does the private chef bring waitstaff?
Depending on the size of your group, the chef might bring waitstaff at their discretion. If you definitely want waitstaff, simply mention this in your request and ask the chef to include this in their quote.
What is the minimum spend
Personal and private chefs on yhangry set their own minimum spend which ranges depending on the chefs experience. The lowest minimum spend by any chef on the platform is £200, the majority of chefs have a minimum spend between £500-£1000. Some chefs have a minimum spend of £3000.
Are the chefs insured?
Yes, all our chefs are covered by public liability insurance for bookings made on the yhangry platform.
Do Yhangry private chefs clean up after cooking?
Yes, yhangry private chefs clean up after cooking and leave your kitchen as it was at the start.
What is the cancellation policy?
If you cancel your private chef more than 7 days before your event date, we offer a 100% refund. Exceptions apply for peak days such as Christmas Day (25th Dec) and NYE (31st Dec) - we do not offer refunds for cancellations on those days.
What payment options are available to book a private chef?
We offer 3 different types of payment options:
  1. 1. Pay in full
  2. 2. Pay a 10% deposit: The remaining 90% is charged to your card 1 month before the event date.*
  3. 3. Split the bill: While placing the booking you just pay for yourself. You'll receive an email with a payment link to share with the remaining guests to pay their share. All guest payments from guests need to be settled 1 month prior to the event date.*

*Only available if your event date is more than 5 weeks away.
#### Still have questions?
Can't find the answer you're looking for? Please chat to our friendly team.

## Why hire private chef for your event with yhangry
### Vetted and rated professional chefs
We work with the best chefs and we make choosing the right chef easy by providing transparent ratings and reviews by real customers.
### Secure payment & protection
At Yhangry, all payments are securely held in escrow until after your event. This ensures your funds are protected, minimizing any risks. Whether your concern is a no-show chef or a bad experience, pay securely through the platform for peace of mind.
### Public liability insurance cover
Any accidents, caused by the chef during an event booked on the yhangry platform is covered by our public liability policy. We’ve made it our mission to give you peace of mind.
### BNPL or split the bill with your guests
If you are booking your event more than 5 weeks in advance, you can pay a 10% deposit or use our split bill feature instead of making the full payment upfront.
### Flexible cancellation policy
If a chef cancels, we will help you find a new chef and if that’s not possible you will receive a full refund, no need to worry about losing any money. If you need to cancel, you will get a 100% refund until 7 days before your event.

## Frequently asked questions
#### Still have questions?
Can't find the answer you're looking for? Please chat to our friendly team.
Contact us⟨34⟩
How much is a private/personal chef in the UK?
Customers booking a private or personal chef for an event usually spend £700 for a group of 10 people. The per person pricing varies depending on the number of people and the particular chef's minimum spend.
What is included in the costs of a private chef?
The cost of a private chef covers the cost of Ingredients, meal preparation, cooking, serving, and cleanup.
What equipment do I need to provide for the private chefs?
Mostly yhangry private chefs carry their own equipment, so you won't need to assist with any. However, ensuring the basic cooking amenities like blenders, stoves and crockery are available is essential.
Do I need to provide ingredients or the private chef will get it?
You can provide your own ingredients if you're seeking to lower the overall expense. However, yhangry private chefs mostly bring their own freshly-sourced ingredients and premium-quality meats to prepare scrumptious meals.
What type of ingredients do the private chefs use?
Most chefs have their favourite suppliers for specific produce. Simply ask the chef you're looking to book about where they source their produce and let them know if you have a particular preference, e.g. for organic ingredients.
Does the private chef bring waitstaff?
Depending on the size of your group, the chef might bring waitstaff at their discretion. If you definitely want waitstaff, simply mention this in your request and ask the chef to include this in their quote.
What is the minimum spend
Personal and private chefs on yhangry set their own minimum spend which ranges depending on the chefs experience. The lowest minimum spend by any chef on the platform is £200, the majority of chefs have a minimum spend between £500-£1000. Some chefs have a minimum spend of £3000.
Are the chefs insured?
Yes, all our chefs are covered by public liability insurance for bookings made on the yhangry platform.
Do Yhangry private chefs clean up after cooking?
Yes, yhangry private chefs clean up after cooking and leave your kitchen as it was at the start.
What is the cancellation policy?
If you cancel your private chef more than 7 days before your event date, we offer a 100% refund. Exceptions apply for peak days such as Christmas Day (25th Dec) and NYE (31st Dec) - we do not offer refunds for cancellations on those days.
What payment options are available to book a private chef?
We offer 3 different types of payment options:
  1. 1. Pay in full
  2. 2. Pay a 10% deposit: The remaining 90% is charged to your card 1 month before the event date.*
  3. 3. Split the bill: While placing the booking you just pay for yourself. You'll receive an email with a payment link to share with the remaining guests to pay their share. All guest payments from guests need to be settled 1 month prior to the event date.*

*Only available if your event date is more than 5 weeks away.

**Yhangry: A New Way to Dine at Home**

Founded in 2020 and rocking the Y Combinator Batch W22, Yhangry is based in London, UK. It’s not just another food delivery service; it’s a private chef marketplace that has made it effortless to book a talented chef right to your home for various occasions.

**The Concept**: Yhangry offers a seamless solution to anyone wanting to socialise over a home-cooked meal. For approximately $40 per person, patrons can secure a three-course feast—with minimal clicks. Think of it as taking the restaurant experience up a notch: instead of navigating crowded spaces, you get fine dining in the comfort of your own home. 

On the flip side, it’s a lucrative path for chefs. Yhangry helps culinary professionals earn up to three times more than typical restaurant roles, creating a win-win scenario.

**How it Works**:
1. **Personalised Experience**: Users specify their preferences, vibe, and budget. 
2. **Curated Quotes**: Within about 20 minutes, clients receive tailored menus and quotes from various chefs.
3. **Customisation**: After booking, customers can still tweak their menus through direct chats with their chef.

**Diverse Offerings**: The platform is a treasure trove for food lovers. Whether you're hosting a birthday party, wedding, or a casual get-together, the chefs create bespoke menus tailored to individual tastes. The options range from vegan meals, international cuisines, fine dining experiences, to kid-friendly menus—there’s something for every palate.

**Why Choose Yhangry?**
- **Vetted and Rated Chefs**: Each chef comes with a transparent rating and review system, ensuring quality.
- **Secure Payment**: All payments are safely held until the event, minimising risk.
- **Insurance**: Public liability insurance covers any mishaps during the chef’s service.
